<APID>TH-1961-32807-10581-75</APID>
<IMGSIZE>3083,4153</IMGSIZE>
<PLACE><ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Cattaraugus</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">New York</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">United States</ENAMEX></PLACE>
<SBODY>5 6 3
WARRANTY <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">DEED</ENAMEX>.
This <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">Indenture</ENAMEX>, Made this ⌨⌨⌨⌨⌨⌨⌨ <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Joseph ⌨⌨</ENAMEX>⌨⌨⌨ ⌨ M. <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">wife</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Fredonia</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">N.Y.</ENAMEX>
of the first part, and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Emara L. Thompson</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Randolph</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">N.Y.</ENAMEX>
of the second part
Witnesseth, That the said party of the first part, in consideration of the sum of <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">eighteen hundred
Dollars</NUMEX>,
to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">them</ENAMEX> duly paid, have sold, and by these presents do grant and convey to the said party of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX>
and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>, ALL THAT Tudor of Pamont of LAND, situate in the ⌨own of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Conewago County</ENAMEX> and State aforesaid
distinguished by being a part of lot number one, township three range side of the
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE.notgpe">Holland Land Companys</ENAMEX> survey and bounded as follows, Beginning at a point in
the center of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE.notgpe">Elmn Creek</ENAMEX> highway <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">twenty seven</NUMEX> links northerly from the south
east corner of land deeded by <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Johnson V. Goodwill</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">wife</ENAMEX> to <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Merrill T. Jenkins</ENAMEX>. 
thence reading northerly along the center of said highway <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">one</NUMEX> chain <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">ninety eight</NUMEX>.
links to land owned by <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Bishop</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Williams</ENAMEX>: thence westerly along the south line of
said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Williams</ENAMEX> load <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">seven</NUMEX> chains <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">thirty seven</NUMEX> links to land owned by <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">George Watkins</ENAMEX> 
thence southerly on the east line of said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Walkins</ENAMEX> land <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">one</NUMEX> chains <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">ninety</NUMEX> links
to land owned by <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">George Watkias</ENAMEX>: thence easterly along the north line of said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Watkins</ENAMEX> 
land <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">seven</NUMEX> chains <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">thirty seven</NUMEX> links to the place of beginning containing <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">one and
one half</NUMEX> acres of land be the same more or less.
With the Bow purtenanfPS, and all the estate, title and interest therein of the said party of the first part. And the said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Joseph M. Congdon</ENAMEX>
does hereby covenant and agree to and with the said party of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>
that the premises thus conveyed, in the quiet and peaceable possession of the said party of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">he</ENAMEX>
will forever WARRANT AND DEFEND against any person <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">whomsoever</ENAMEX> lawfully claiming the same or any part thereof ated to or <ENAMEX TYPE="AGE">age of 12</ENAMEX> in the Waters
Jn Witness whereof, The parties of the first part, have hereunto set <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> hands and seals the <TIMEX TYPE="COREF.dat">day and year first above written</TIMEX>.
Sealed and Delivered in Presence of
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Joseph M. Congdon</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Alice M. Congdon</ENAMEX> tha<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">STATE OF NEW YORK</ENAMEX>, =RCB= s.
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">ORNEYS</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">COUNTY of Plantation</ENAMEX> <TIMEX TYPE="DATE.non">May four</TIMEX> on and ┃ <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Joseph McCongdon</ENAMEX> ⌨⌨⌨⌨ to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX> known to be the same persons described in and <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">who</ENAMEX> executed the within
instrument, and severally acknowledged that <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">they</ENAMEX> executed the same; and the said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Olice M. Congdon</ENAMEX>
on a private examination by <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX>, apart from <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> said <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">husband</ENAMEX> acknowledged that the executed the same freely, and without any fear or compulsion of <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> said <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">husband</ENAMEX>.
<ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">County Judge</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Chautauqua County</ENAMEX>,
of the decree of <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Counsel at Law</ENAMEX>
dered mind and toward the crowd the
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">E. A. Nash</ENAMEX>
</SBODY>
</NBX>
